# Public RFP repository boundary

`WindhorseTour/wht-2026-retheme-rfp` is the **public bidding** repo. Private vendor evaluation lives in a **separate** procurement repository and must **never** appear here.

## Never add, copy, link, or commit

- The `wht-2026-retheme-procurement/` directory or any clone/checkout of the private procurement repo
- Vendor scorecards, vendor notes, or files under `vendors/` from procurement
- Executed/signed NDAs (`*EXECUTED*.pdf`, signed PDFs, signature certificates)
- Vendor proposals, bid analysis, or correspondence meant for internal evaluation
- README or docs links to the private procurement repo or its GitHub URL
- Paths like `documents/nda/`, `documents/proposals/` when they contain evaluation material

## Allowed here

- Public RFP, Q&A log, reference files, NDA **template** (`03-legal/NDA-template.md`), commercial template, workflow docs

## Before any git commit or push

1. Run `git status` and inspect every added/changed path.
2. If any path matches the forbidden list above, **stop** — do not commit or push.
3. Do not use `git add -f` to bypass `.gitignore` for procurement or evaluation files.

## If asked to log vendor NDAs, proposals, or evaluation work

Refuse in this repo. Tell the user to use the private procurement repository instead.
